<p align="center"><font size="3"><strong>Job Openings</strong></font></p>
<p align="left">The Richland Parish School Board is currently accepting applications for:</p>
<p align="left"><strong>Principal</strong><br>(Applicant pool may be used to fill upcoming 2020-21 vacancies)<br>
Applicant must have at minimum:</p>
<ul class="requirements">
<li>5 years of successful teaching experience</li>
<li>Educational Leadership Certificate or Principal certification</li>
<li>Master's degree in Education</li>
</ul>
Leadership experience is preferred.

<p align="left"><strong>Assistant Principal/Assistant Principal Intern</strong><br>(Applicant pool may be used to fill upcoming 2020-21 vacancies)<br>
Applicant must have at minimum:</p>
<ul class="requirements">
<li>5 years of successful teaching experience</li>
<li>Valid Louisiana teaching certificate</li>
<li>Educational leader/ principal certification is preferred/ or
enrollment in a Maste's Degree Program working towards educational leader
certification is required</li>
</ul>
<p align="left">Applications can be accessed from
the school district website www.richland.k12.la.us, or by visiting the
central office complex.  Application should be directed by email to
personnel@richland.k12.la.us, by visiting the central office complex, or by
mail to:
</p>
<div style="padding-left: 50px; font-size: 9pt; line-height: normal;">
		Director of Personnel<br>
		Richland Parish School Board<br>
		411 Foster Street<br>
		P.O. Box 599<br>
		Rayville, LA 71269<br>
</div>
<p align="left">Applications must be received no later than 4:00 p.m. on Friday, May 8, 2020.</p>
